<doc id="1012308" wikidata="Q3283658" url="?curid=1012308" title="Bankekind">
<text>Bankekind is a locality situated in Linköping Municipality, Östergötland County, Sweden with 405 inhabitants in 2010. Bankekind was earlier called &quot;Svinstad&quot; (ENG: &quot;Pigtown&quot;) but changed its name because of the pejorative connotations. It is known for its 13th-century church and the lake Svinstadsjön.
It is primarily a commuter village but had its own nursery/ pre-school, primary school (school years, 0-3) and supported housing residence for the elderly.

&quot;Bankekinds härad&quot; (&quot;Bankekind Hundred&quot;) was a hundred of Östergötland in Sweden.

